TITLE: Under Armour stock falls as company offers weak guidance, posts unexpected loss
SUMMARY: Under Armour reported an unexpected loss and sales below estimates as the company grappled with global supply chain challenges and Covid lockdowns in China.

TITLE: DoorDash rises after reporting 35% sales growth
SUMMARY: DoorDash reported a significantly slower rate of revenue growth than it did in the same quarter in 2021, when net sales nearly tripled.

TITLE: Lucid reports 30,000 EV reservations and raises prices on its Air sedans
SUMMARY: Lucid said that it now has 30,000 reservations for its Air luxury sedan — and it's raising prices in June.

TITLE: Sweetgreen losses widen despite 67% jump in quarterly sales
SUMMARY: Sweetgreen sales jumped 67%, fueled by more customer transactions and menu price hikes.

TITLE: Nikola stock jumps as EV truck maker reports start to production and surprise Q1 revenue
SUMMARY: Nikola reported a Q1 loss per share that was narrower than Wall Street expected and confirmed that its fuel cell truck is on track for a 2023 launch.

TITLE: Shopify stock sinks 15% after earnings miss, $2.1 billion acquisition of logistics start-up
SUMMARY: Shopify announced it would buy Deliverr, which provides fulfillment services for online merchants, for $2.1 billion, the largest acquisition in its history.

TITLE: Wayfair loses customers and money in a messy quarter, announces its CFO will retire
SUMMARY: Wayfair co-founder and Chief Executive Officer Niraj Shah said, despite sliding sales, consumer health remains "relatively strong."

TITLE: Oil giant Shell reports highest quarterly profit since 2008 on soaring commodity prices
SUMMARY: Shell's bumper earnings echo profits seen across the oil and gas industry, even as many energy majors incur costly write-downs from exiting Russia.

TITLE: Sunrun shares surge after company reports jump in customers, says higher utility prices are fueling solar
SUMMARY: The largest residential solar company in the U.S. raised guidance for Q2 as soaring commodity prices make solar power more attractive.

TITLE: EBay and Etsy drop on weak guidance as e-commerce crunch continues
SUMMARY: Both of the companies gave disappointing guidance for the current quarter, sending their stocks sharply lower in extended trading.

TITLE: A slate of EV automakers report earnings this week and will try to prove they can turn hype into production
SUMMARY: All three stocks are down sharply from highs: Can the companies regain momentum?

TITLE: Moderna blows out first-quarter earnings expectations, triples Covid vaccine sales
SUMMARY: Moderna's first-quarter vaccine sales more than tripled over the same period last year, when it reported $1.7 billion in sales.

TITLE: Yum Brands earnings miss estimates as China weighs on KFC, Pizza Hut sales
SUMMARY: Taco Bell was the only chain in Yum's portfolio to report better-than-expected same-store sales growth.

TITLE: Uber reports surging revenue as drivers return, but posts massive loss on investments
SUMMARY: Uber expects to keep drivers without "significant incremental incentive investments."

TITLE: CVS raises forecast for year, as first-quarter earnings top expectations
SUMMARY: CVS Health beat expectations for earnings and raised its guidance for the year, as it saw demand for prescriptions and more, as demand for Covid testing fell.

TITLE: Starbucks suspends its outlook as Covid lockdowns hammer sales in China
SUMMARY: It's Howard Schultz's first earnings report since taking back the top job at Starbucks in early April.

TITLE: AMD sales jump 71%, shrugging off concerns about PC slowdown
SUMMARY: AMD reported first-quarter earnings after the bell on Tuesday, beating analyst estimates for earnings and revenue.

TITLE: Lyft shares plunge on light guidance, continued driver incentives
SUMMARY: The company has struggled with driver supply and demand imbalances throughout the pandemic, leading to higher costs or long wait times.

TITLE: Airbnb beats estimates with 70% revenue growth as travel rebounds
SUMMARY: Airbnb said it's seen substantial growth in bookings despite pandemic concerns, "macroeconomic headwinds" and the war in Ukraine.

TITLE: Pfizer cuts 2022 earnings outlook despite strong first-quarter Covid vaccine and antiviral sales
SUMMARY: Pfizer said it sold $13.2 billion of its Covid vaccine and $1.5 billion of its antiviral treatment Paxlovid.

TITLE: Burger King parent earnings beat estimates as revenue climbs 15%
SUMMARY: Restaurant Brands International reported results that beat expectations, fueled by strong same-store sales growth from Burger King's overseas restaurants.

TITLE: BP reports bumper first-quarter net profit, but posts massive loss on hit from Russia exit
SUMMARY: BP announced a further $2.5 billion in share buybacks as it reported its highest first-quarter profit in more than a decade.

TITLE: Uber reports first-quarter earnings on Wednesday: Here's what Wall Street's watching
SUMMARY: Uber shares are down more than 26% year to date. Here's what Wall Street will be looking for when Uber reports first-quarter earnings on Wednesday.

TITLE: Berkshire earnings decline in the first quarter on slowing economic growth, stock market pullback
SUMMARY: Warren Buffett's Berkshire Hathaway reported Saturday a decline in first-quarter earnings, as the conglomerate was not immune to a slowing U.S. economy.

TITLE: Amazon shares fall on bleak forecast and slowest growth since dot-com bust
SUMMARY: Amazon gave a revenue forecast that trailed analysts' estimates and recorded a big loss on its Rivian investment.

TITLE: Apple shares dip after company warns of a possible $8 billion hit from supply constraints
SUMMARY: Apple reported earnings after the bell. Here are the results.

TITLE: Intel beats but offers disappointing guidance
SUMMARY: Intel called for weaker-than-expected second-quarter earnings and revenue as it plans exapansion through factories in the U.S. and Germany.

TITLE: Robinhood reports shrinking revenue, fewer active users
SUMMARY: Robinhood was up against some tough comparisons in the first quarter, when interest in so-called meme stocks in 2021 fueled its rapid growth.

TITLE: Twitter reports user bump, revenue miss for Q1, days after accepting Musk's takeover bid
SUMMARY: Twitter just reported earnings for the first quarter of 2022, in what could be one of its last public reports after its board agreed to sell to Elon Musk.

TITLE: Merck sold $3.2 billion of its Covid oral antiviral treatment, driving first-quarter revenue growth
SUMMARY: Merck soundly beat Wall Street estimates for its top and bottom lines, reporting earnings of $2.14 per share on $15.9 billion in revenue.
